    "media:imagetext": "THE NEW CLIPPER A\nMERICA\nBREAKFAST IN BED\nFour day-time chairs open out in berths seven inches wider and\nfour inches longer than the standard Pullman accommodations. The berths\ntake only a few minutes to make up. Breakfast is served in bed over the\nAtlantic or Pacific or wherever the traveler happens to be overnighting.\nSince most of the world is not much more than a night's hop in this new\nClipper, the addition of berths to regulation airline accommodations will\nbanish time and space and boredom.\nPAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS\n135 East 42nd Street\nNew York 17, New York\nMUrray Hill\n6-7100\nFor Immediate Release",
